{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17533194","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17533194"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T16:33:31+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T16:33:31+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14763"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17584648","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17584648"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:52:47+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:52:47+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14763"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14763","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14763"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.01,0.03,0.87,0.04,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7454"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"58466"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7454","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7454"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14763"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"43882"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"3639"},{"type":"tags","id":"3675"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18233"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"58466","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/58466"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 28-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic seeking advice before trying to conceive. She and her partner are planning a holiday to Brazil in three months. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. She has heard about Zika virus in the news and is concerned about risks of infection. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most common mode of Zika virus transmission?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Blood transfusion","Sexual contact","Infected mosquito bite","Direct person-to-person contact","Mother-to-child transmission"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EZika virus is primarily transmitted through the bite of infected mosquitoes, particularly \u003Cem\u003EAedes aegypti\u003C/em\u003E and \u003Cem\u003EAedes albopictus\u003C/em\u003E. These mosquitoes are also responsible for transmitting dengue and chikungunya viruses. \u003Cstrong\u003EInfected mosquito bite\u003C/strong\u003E accounts for the majority of Zika virus infections worldwide.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESexual contact\u003C/strong\u003E is a documented mode of transmission, particularly from male to female partners. The virus can persist in semen for several months after infection, which is why travel advice includes recommendations about safe sex practices after visiting Zika-endemic areas.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlood transfusion\u003C/strong\u003E transmission is possible but rare. Some countries have implemented blood donor screening in Zika-endemic areas to reduce this risk.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMother-to-child transmission\u003C/strong\u003E can occur during pregnancy or around the time of birth. This is particularly concerning as it can lead to congenital Zika syndrome, characterised by microcephaly and other developmental abnormalities.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDirect person-to-person contact\u003C/strong\u003E through casual contact is not a mode of transmission for Zika virus. The virus requires a vector (mosquito) or specific body fluid exposure (sexual contact, blood, or vertical transmission) for transmission to occur.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Zika virus is primarily transmitted through the bite of infected Aedes mosquitoes, particularly Aedes aegypti.","Sexual transmission and vertical transmission of Zika virus are important non-vector modes of transmission."],"references":["Musso D, Ko AI, Baud D. Zika Virus Infection - After the Pandemic. N Engl J Med. 2019;381(15):1444-1457. doi:10.1056/NEJMra1808246","Pierson TC, Diamond MS. The emergence of Zika virus and its new clinical syndromes. Nature. 2018;560(7720):573-581. doi:10.1038/s41586-018-0446-y"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"43882"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14763"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"43882","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/43882"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-10-31T19:06:34+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-31T19:07:22+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7454"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"58466"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:51:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"3639","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/3639"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Zika virus","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-09-23T21:58:47+09:30","updatedAt":"20